2) k-Nearest Neighbors: k-Nearest Neighbors [2] or k-NN is a non-parametric technique which is used for classiﬁcation. In this technique, k closest neighbours to each input is found and the input is classiﬁed based on the majority vote of its nearest neighbors. In this paper, Mahalonobis metric is used to calculate the distance of sample which is deﬁned as

d(x, y) = (x − y)T M (x − y)

